</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR218:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR218"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              218-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 218</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Ramos<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>June 03, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to the Huuc Atam Highway. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 218, as introduced, Ramos.
                          The Huuc Atam Highway.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate a specified portion of State Route 18 in the County of San Bernardino as the Huuc Atam Highway. The measure would request that the Department of Transportation determine the cost of appropriate signs showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_743FE682-28AA-47B1-AECC-7A6019B69AE5"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Yuhaaviatam of San Manuel Nation, also known as the San Manuel Band of Mission Indians, is a federally recognized sovereign Indian tribe located on the San Manuel Indian Reservation in the County of San Bernardino near Highland, California; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7BAFD2D5-782C-4307-BC59-239490FFAFAC"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Yuhaaviatam of San Manuel Nation proudly reclaims its ancestral name, Yuhaaviatam, pronounced as “yu-HAH-vee-ah-tahm,” honoring the deep-rooted heritage and enduring legacy of its people; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F7CA3980-4DC0-4481-93DD-D79447E64502"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Exercising its inherent sovereign right to self-governance, the Yuhaaviatam is committed to providing essential services to its citizens by building infrastructure, maintaining civil services, and promoting social, economic, and cultural development; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_ABD61763-1C65-4A85-9220-D8324D265226"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, As the Indigenous people of the San Bernardino highlands, passes, valleys, mountains and high deserts, Yuhaaviatam of San Manuel Nation has called this region home since time immemorial and are committed to remaining a productive partner in the San Bernardino region; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0BBB4324-749D-43D7-BEAC-EF6E4FBCD8BD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Yuhaaviatam is one of the clans of the Maara’yam, pronounced as “MAH-ra-yahm,” the larger group of people from whom the tribe’s citizens descend and who is broadly referred to also as Serrano people; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_EC2B5ACC-B626-40EF-AF99-04164CAFECEA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Huuc Atam is the Maara’yam traditional name for the Arrowhead landmark that is the namesake of Arrowhead Springs; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E657C7F0-32D9-41FB-939F-72E023DD16D3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, “Huuc Atam” translates to arrowhead, which literally means “tooth of the arrow”; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_CD40CCD7-3462-41A1-8872-08DFF7691C35"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Arrowhead is a natural landmark that measures 1,375 feet long and 449 feet wide and can be seen from miles around; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_5F8C8CA5-31AB-457B-9D6C-9E125A2A4598"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Arrowhead is sacred to Yuhaaviatam of San Manuel Nation and plays an important part in the Maara’yam culture; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_106C9266-9112-4BDC-B168-D25F419D8C50"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Maara’yam tradition holds that the Arrowhead was placed there by the Creator; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_A6AF73E7-7B9D-45B3-8BFD-C6F02014CBFF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates the portion of State Route 18 in the County of San Bernardino from the junction with State Route 210, at postmile T6.179, to the Old Waterman Canyon Road, at postmile 9.150, as the Huuc Atam Highway; and be it further </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_21E41D4B-AE0C-4683-93D8-C3027BE2BC10"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Department of Transportation is requested to determine the cost of appropriate signs, consistent with the signing requirements for the state highway system, showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs; and be it further </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_B058543C-F05A-4B78-BC38-E2FD1762BD4C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the Director of Transportation and to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
